-- Alliant Energy Names COO Kampling to Become CEO and Chairman
-- B y   M a r k   C h e d i a k
-- 2012-01-20T22:55:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/alliant-energy-names-coo-kampling-to-become-ceo-and-chairman.html
Alliant Energy Corp. (LNT)  named Patricia Kampling as its new chairman and chief executive officer to
succeed CEO William Harvey,  who will retire on March 31.  Kampling, 52, who now serves as president and chief
operating officer, will take over as CEO effective April 1, the
Madison, Wisconsin-based company said in a statement.  Harvey is retiring after 25 years with Alliant, serving as
CEO and chairman during the last six years, the statement said.
Kampling, who joined Alliant in 2005, previously worked at units
of  Exelon Corp. (EXC)   To contact the reporter on this story:
